  "body": "# submission name:\nhnerv_muon_lc\n\n# upload zipped `archive.zip`\nhttps://github.com/BradyMeighan/comma_video_compression_challenge/releases/download/hnerv-muon-lc-archive/archive.zip\n\n# report.txt\n```\n=== Evaluation config ===\n  batch_size: 16\n  device: cpu\n  num_threads: 2\n  prefetch_queue_depth: 4\n  report: submissions/hnerv_muon_lc/report.txt\n  seed: 1234\n  submission_dir: submissions/hnerv_muon_lc\n  uncompressed_dir: ./videos\n  video_names_file: ./public_test_video_names.txt\n=== Evaluation results over 600 samples ===\n  Average PoseNet Distortion: 0.00003349\n  Average SegNet Distortion: 0.00059494\n  Submission file size: 178,546 bytes\n  Original uncompressed size: 37,545,489 bytes\n  Compression Rate: 0.00475546\n  Final score: 100*segnet_dist + √(10*posenet_dist) + 25*rate = 0.20\n```\nExact CI score: `0.19667`.\n\n# does your submission require gpu for evaluation (inflation)?\nno\n\n# did you include the compression script? and want it to be merged?\nno\n\n# additional comments\n\nThis is a re-pack of @AaronLeslie138's `hnerv_muon` archive (PR #95) with two layered improvements on top of his trained HNeRV decoder + latents:\n\n1. **Schema-driven INT8 repack** (~480 B saved on the decoder section). His decoder ships full layer-name strings + per-tensor shape arrays + fp32 scales inline (~1 KB metadata before brotli). We move the schema (28 tensor names + shapes) into our Python decoder and ship only fp16 scales (56 B) + a single concatenated INT8 codes blob, brotli'd. Bit-exact dequant.\n\n2. **Latent-correction sidecar** (615 B brotli'd). Per-pair single-dim perturbation of his 28-d HNeRV latents. We grid-search (dim ∈ 0..27) × (δ ∈ {±0.02, ±0.05, ±0.10}) and pick the (dim, δ) that minimizes the joint per-pair loss `100·seg_dist + α·pose_dist`, where α = √10 / (2·√mean_pose_baseline) ≈ 270 balances marginal score impact at his baseline. 598/600 pairs get a non-trivial correction, encoded as `(u8 dim, i8 quant_δ_×100)` and brotli'd. Both seg and pose distortion drop (seg 0.000612 → 0.000595, pose 0.0000349 → 0.0000334).\n\nNotes:\n- All weights, the architecture, the 8-stage curriculum, the C1a regularizer and the Muon training are @AaronLeslie138's. Our contribution is purely byte-level (schema repack) plus inference-time latent correction (sidecar). Inflate path bit-exact dequantizes his INT8 weights, then perturbs latents per the sidecar before running his decoder unchanged.\n- We tried F1 warps (the technique from our `vibe_coder_final_boss` submission, PR #97) — they did NOT transfer to HNeRV. His model is positionally aligned with GT; the seg distortion comes from blur, not translation, so warps can't fix it (verified on the worst 30 pairs: best warp was always (0,0)).\n- We tried lower-bit quant (INT7/INT6) — broke his QAT (INT7 → score 0.18, INT6 → 0.29). His training is razor-thin at INT8.\n- Pixel-level tweaks (brightness/gamma/blur+unsharp) on top of the latent corrections didn't pay back their sidecar bytes either.\n- Reproduced via the same eval.yml workflow on a fork before submitting: https://github.com/BradyMeighan/comma_video_compression_challenge/actions/runs/25311463434 (15m on ubuntu-latest CPU).\n\nSource: https://github.com/BradyMeighan/comma_video_compression_challenge/tree/submission/hnerv_muon_lc\n",
